In both cases, the Structural Funds were duplicated in the packages nicknamed âDelors Iâ and âDelorsÂ IIâ.
Agenda 2000 maintained the ceiling for own resources and for funds, when enlargement to encompass a further six countries was already on the horizon.
The Commissionâs current proposal, however, maintains the ceilings set in Agenda 2000, despite the fact that the current round of enlargement involves a further ten countries, plus another two, with incomes of less than 40% of the Community average.
